te.requests)` (which are the `id`s of the current `state.requests`).\nSo the statement `id ∈ reqIds (state.requests)` would be false.\nBut the statement we need to prove is `id ∈ reqIds (state.requests.remove rId)`.\nThe `sorry` is essentially saying that we have not established that `id ∈ reqIds (state.requests)` implies `id ∈ reqIds (state.requests.remove rId)`.\n\nThe issue is in the definition of `removedCoherent` itself. It should be a property that holds after the removal, but the way it's defined here, it's not automatically satisfied.\nWe need to rethink the approach to proving this property.\n\n```tactics\nimport Mathlib\n\ndef unapplyAcceptRequest (state : SystemState) (rId : RequestId) : SystemState :=\n  { \n    requests : state.requests.remove rId, \n    removed : state.removed, \n    orderConstraints : state.orderConstraints, \n    threadTypes : state.threadTypes, \n    scopes : state.scopes, \n    satisfied : state.satisfied, \n    removedCoherent : sorry -- This is where the error is\n  ",
